p:::s35:::Nagg asks her to kiss him ; they try but can not reach , and Nell asks why they go through the `` farce '' every day .
p:::s38:::Nell rebukes Nagg for laughing at Hamm 's misery .
p:::s39:::Nagg tells her a story about a tailor that has often made her laugh , especially the first time he told it to the day after they 'd gotten engaged : a tailor keeps botching and delaying a customer 's orders for trousers until the customer explodes and points out that God created the world in six days , while the tailor has taken three months for the trousers .
p:::s80:::He knocks on Nell 's lid , but with no response he retreats into his bin and closes the lid .
p:::s85:::He tells Clov to see if Nell is dead ; he looks into the bin and says it looks that way .
